The paper deals with pedestrian detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses optimization and compression techniques for the network, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the detector in automotive safety suggests a possible connection to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between accuracy and memory usage, which could be relevant to computer security (cs.CR).
